com.ibm.team.scm.common

Interface IWorkspace

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IContextHandle, IFlowNode, IFlowNodeHandle, com.ibm.team.scm.common.IHistoryReference, IItem, IItemHandle, IManagedItem, IManagedItemHandle, ISimpleItem, ISimpleItemHandle, IWorkspaceHandle

    public interface IWorkspace
extends IWorkspaceHandle, IFlowNode
    Represents a workspace qua auditable item.

    Notes:

    • All interesting protocol for working with workspace is available via { IWorkspaceConnection.
    • The protocol exposed here is for examining a workspace item's audit history.
    • Clients cannot create workspace auditables in the normal fashion. Creating workspace can only be done with special methods on IWorkspaceConnection.
    • The workspace auditable has additional properties that are not exposed to clients.

    Feature access profile values:

    • name: SMALL
    • history: DEFAULT
    • lock: SMALL
    • owner: DEFAULT
    • vtime: SMALL

    Since:
    0.5

      • STREAM_LOCK_OWNER_USER_ID_PROPERTY_KEY

        static final java.lang.String STREAM_LOCK_OWNER_USER_ID_PROPERTY_KEY
        Property key for the stream lock owner's user id. If the stream is not locked, the property will not exist, or will be an empty string. The user id may not not be present even if the stream is locked. Key begins with the reserved "scm" prefix.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • STREAM_LOCK_OWNER_USER_NAME_PROPERTY_KEY

        static final java.lang.Object STREAM_LOCK_OWNER_USER_NAME_PROPERTY_KEY
        Property key for the stream lock owner's Jazz user name. If the stream is not locked, the property will not exist, or will be an empty string This is a convenience so that the client does not need to continuously look up the Jazz user name for the contributor id. Key begins with the reserved "scm" prefix.

      • getProperties

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getProperties()
        Returns a read-only map of properties. Properties are keyed by a non-empty key. Key's are restricted to being between 1 and 128 characters. The prefix "scm:" is reserved for internal use of Jazz Source Control, so downstream components and user cannot use this prefix in their keys. Property values can be set to empty or non-empty values. The keys and values in this map are considered opaque by the RTC server. URIs should not be placed in this map if the user/caller is expecting these URIs to be portable after data configuration. We do not provide any introspection on these values. This map should not be used for any identifiers which are not immediate attributes of this item. It is not recommended that these fields are used to store references to other items in the repository, as this could impact the state when it gets replicated to another repository.
        Since:
        0.8.0 (RTC 3.0)

      • isLocked

        boolean isLocked()
        Return true if the receiver is locked, false otherwise. This is a persistent lock to prevent delivery to the stream. It is not the transactional lock like the ones on component entries. At this time, only stream can be locked, not repository workspaces.
        Returns:
        the lock status of the receiver
        Since:
        0.11.0.2 (RTC 6.0.2)
